values:
I have an Adam in my bed. &hearts;

I am. The happiest Theos in the whole world. 

When he arrived, I ran out to the lobby of my building to meet him. I just kinda jumped in his arms and he lifted me up and spun me around and we refused to let go for like five minutes. &hearts; It was like a movie. It really, really was.

Just. Gah. I smell like him. &hearts; 

Soooo, so happy. This is what I've been waiting for. :3

I'm wondering... what is the <i>exact</i> shamanistic belief about the afterlife? I mean, I know that they believe in ancestral spirits and all that. But, specifically, what happens to the spirits who... well, in Christian equivalent, would be rotting in hell. >.>;! 

I may or may not be writing a Thrall/Jaina/Arthas fic thing lulz.

Work in the AM, then I have a day off, yay &hearts;
